data.name: checkBoxUseHighMemory.ToolTip
data.value: This option will significantly reduce file size of JPEG files, but uses a large amount of memory. During runtime, your PC should have about 300MB of free memory and may take up to 1 minute of processing per 1MP of an image. Default: Unchecked

data.name: numUpDownNoOfPasses.ToolTip
data.value: The number of passes determines how the program attempts to optimize your PNG image. The lower the level, the minifal the effort. The higher the level, the more space you may save but may take more time as it is slower.

data.name: LabelNoOfPasses.ToolTip
data.value:
The number of passes determines how the program attempts to optimize your PNG image. The lower the level, the minifal the effort. The higher the level, the more space you may save but may take more time as it is slower.
Default: 3 passes
